				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Ok, After killing the warden bruke, I went back to persue the 2nd part of the quest, protecting Glacierbane. <BR>
<BR>
This was the most fun I've ever had on a quest. In preparation I (a druid 51) brought a mage 44, cleric 51 and two tanks 42,39 with me. Things went really well after we got started.. Boradain's spawn point appears to be a focal point of pathing so get in and out of there quick if you don't want everything in the area to eventually walk over you. <BR>
<BR>
After giving him the axe, he proclaims that he's a great tracker and will track down the kodiak. First thing he does is walk over to the North Western Giant fort. He walks RIGHT up to the entrance and guess what? attacks the guards at the door. He conned green to a low 30's walking with us so he's gotta be a wimp and in just a couple hits was down to half health. We dispatched the guard and the dwarf started walking again. He then took a short break and sat down. At this point we're all in stiches laughing at this little guy. He gets up and then walks over to the Giant Prison by the Ulthorks and attacks a rygorr and giant who are in one of those &quot;pens&quot; in that area. We got rid of those and he walked off to the Rygorr fort. <BR>
<BR>
At this point you'll want to tell those in front of the fort that you're coming. If anyone is in Wolf Form or Werewolf form, that stupid little dwarf will attack them. Unless it's a FD-class in wolf form, they'll have to zone or you'll have to start over. <BR>
<BR>
After walking up to the entrance of the Rygorr fort, he goes RIGHT BACK TO WHERE HE STARTED and claims that he must stink as a tracker. Well behind him the kodiak then spawns. An easy kill to us. <BR>
<BR>
Now the dwarf despawned on me so I'm hoping I can turn in the pelt to him without him holding the axe..i'll post when i know.<BR>
<BR>
At this point I was rolling in laughter from my tank
